  <li id="comment-39292" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">kiki</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39292"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-06T04:46:12-05:00">Sunday, January 6, 2013 at 4:46 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;ve been there, and it sucked. And the hardest part about it all is the way in which you feel so overwhelmed so that even the most minimal of self-care (like getting help) seems too much. I&#39;m glad it wasn&#39;t for you. I think we aren&#39;t honest enough with new mothers about how hard and isolating and lonely the work of motherhood often is. Other people have walked this path. And it does get better. </p>
<p>I&#39;m due with #2 any day now. And I am worried. I&#39;ve also resolved to find help this time, as soon as I need it. I&#39;m afraid of the shadow, but unwilling to let it steal the sun, you know?</p>
<p>Hugs to you.</p>
