  <li id="comment-39771" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/09680224223707023918" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Sara</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39771"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-06T21:00:17-05:00">Sunday, January 6, 2013 at 9:00 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;m so glad you trust us all enough to share.  Even without postpartum depression, many women just seem to feel like they can&#39;t admit that things aren&#39;t always gloriously perfect when you have a baby.  It is hard.  And we all have a LOT of feelings.  And we have to get better at supporting each other so that we can enjoy those beautiful moments when the light is just so perfect&#8230;</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
