    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have to join the chorus of &#8220;thank you&#8221;s. I started following your blog just before I became pregnant with our first, and he was born four days after June. He is beautiful, healthy, hilarious, and everything we ever dared to wish for, my husband is wonderful, our life is great, and I also recently had to admit that I was being sucked under by PPD. It&#39;s humbling, and at first I was really ashamed.   It&#39;s been so helpful to me to hear from other moms about their dark moments, to be reassured that I&#39;m not alone and that I&#39;m not a terrible person for not being happy all the time. </p>
<p>Your daughter is gorgeous. She loves you and knows you love her.  Congratulations on being such a wonderful mother that you were strong enough to get help. </p>
