    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I am relatively new to your blog, Molly, in part because I am entering a stage of life far different from your own and one that is finally offering me the time to do things like read blogs. My children are nearning the end of their teenage years. As I read about your life with a newborn, it brings me back to that overwhelming time of life as a new parent when my life entirely revolved around my children. Yes, babies are adorable and miraculous, but they are also a hell of a lot of work. Judging by the insight you show in your writing, I am guessing that you will work your way through this with your own personal grace and with the help of loved ones. Parenting is a journey that has challenged me physically and emotionally like nothing else. At the same time, I have never gained so much from any other aspect of my life. Thank you for sharing with such honesty.</p>
