  <li id="comment-39425" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">KWJW</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39425"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-07T18:51:44-05:00">Monday, January 7, 2013 at 6:51 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I feel for you on this journey, Molly.  I can&#39;t help wondering this, though &#8212; is it just hormones?  Or is your body/mind telling you something true?  Perhaps you feel overwhelmed because you ARE overwhelmed?  You&#39;ve just opened a new restaurant, you have a book coming out and a Web site to attend to, payrolls to meet and bills to pay, and oh yes, a baby who&#39;s utterly dependent on you for her survival.  And you&#39;re doing all this on very little sleep, I have to assume.  No wonder it&#39;s all coming apart.  So.  Do you have enough help?  Can you get more?  Can you stop doing some things?  Can you remake your life for the next 6 months and just do June?  Some people are born multi-taskers but others &#8212; artists, mostly &#8212; are not.  Artists need to focus. Artists need clarity and alone-time and breathing space and all the things you&#39;re not getting.  So anyway, I hope you can simplify where you can and get help where you can&#39;t.  xx</p>
    </div>

