      <p>From one new mother in Ballard to another, thank you for scraping together the time to write and share. (Honestly, this simple response to your post has been interrupted twice already!) My tiny human was born in June ( and I actually wanted to name her June, except for the timing). Life will never be the same, will it. I remember feeling jealous of your previous post about squeezing in a date with your husband, even a Sunday day date for one hour. Nothing is easy anymore, but I too am learning to ask for and accept help, and to pay better attention to my own emotions and needs. Your post is awesome and thank you for finding the courage to share so personally. Should you find a wild-eyed new mom roaming the streets near your restaurant with a baby strapped to her front, wave hello, and know that you are not alone. </p>
