    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I didn&#39;t recognize it after my first, but was hit doubly hard after weaning my second. I work 60+ hours a week and travel quite a bit for work, and I had a really really hard time admitting that I needed help. Finally did a couple months ago after feeling like I was PMSing 24 hours a day &#8211; crying at the drop of a hat, unattached, indifferent, neglecting self care, short tempered &#8211; and with help I feel more like my old self. However, I surely hope it gets better than this, I want to BE my old self again. So I am right with you &#8211; thanks for sharing. I am still in the dark, trying to find the light. </p>
    </div>

