  <li id="comment-39457" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39457"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-08T16:12:37-05:00">Tuesday, January 8, 2013 at 4:12 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, </p>
<p>I, too, am a loyal reader who has never commented. And one who has suffered greatly after having her first child. My baby is 9 months old now, and for about 2 months I have felt normal. I had forgotten how it felt, and never thought I&#39;d experience it again. It is wonderful, and it does come. I had times when I wanted to hurt myself, my child, when I wanted to leave and run away, times paralyzed with anxiety or depression, when I thought I just couldn&#39;t make it,and always hating myself for all of it. I had a huge support system, as obviously, you do, too. Use that support system, go get massages, take walks, have a drink, go to yoga. whatever YOU need to do, that is what is best for june right now. Don&#39;t compare yourself to other moms who cook bouef bourgignon with a baby to their breast while wearing high heels. It helped me to know that I just needed to be ME and do what was best for my family. I can&#39;t imagine that you&#39;d have time to read all of these comments, but I at least write this to the others like me, who with blurred, teary vision, sit and read everyone&#39;s beautiful words of hope and community. xoxo THANK YOU, MOLLY, for everything. we love you.</p>
<p>sarah </p>
    </div>

