    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Kara</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39461"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-08T19:40:41-05:00">Tuesday, January 8, 2013 at 7:40 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Sometimes knowing is the first step in healing. I didn&#39;t realize until I was on the other side that I had PPD. It didn&#39;t look like I thought and it expressed itself in all consuming anxiety to the point of shaking but I still didn&#39;t get it. It&#39;s such a disservice that us women don&#39;t talk more and support each other. Your body has been through the wringer and there is no set time frame or right way to feel or think. I have a motto &#8220;Do the best you can with the information you have at the time. One foot in front of the other. No regrets.&#8221;  Thanks for your bravery. Kara </p>
    </div>

