  <li id="comment-39462" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Ann vz</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39462"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-08T20:47:46-05:00">Tuesday, January 8, 2013 at 8:47 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly,<br />I have never, ever commented. I read your book years ago and my mom and and I pass your recipes back and forth religiously. I have a 6 year old and 2 year old and I, too, struggled with post partum depression with both of my children. I did not want to admit it and let the depression turn into other complicated emotions because i felt somehow I was stronger than these feelings and could overcome. I have learned now, through a few sessions of counseling to untangle all the emotions I was feeling, a few deep breaths, one major breakdown sobbing on my staircase, and a whole lot of introspection that babies are hard and so is life. It is breathtakingly wonderful, but it is hard. It is also true that hormones are SO crazy but for me, the wonderful birth of my beautiful, healthy children unlocked a lot of grief. I write these words to comfort you because I can hardly articulate the deep sense of peace, security and assurance I now feel about my present and my future as well as my role as a mother. It does get better. I am glad you sought help. If I can offer one more piece of advice, please don&#39;t beat yourself up about it and while it may be hard, please listen to your emotions (although ignore any lies in there of unworthiness or being a bad mother! those are lies my friend). Grief and joy are so intricately woven together. I say these words as gently and humbly as possible and only with the intention of encouraging you. You seem to be an incredibly thoughtful, kind person and I know you will be okay. Please know there are many of us rooting for you and many, many of us women who have experienced similar feelings. Take good care dear Molly and xoxox to June,<br />Ann</p>
    </div>

