  <li id="comment-39471" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/02141270011785790129" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Courtney</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39471"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-09T16:47:34-05:00">Wednesday, January 9, 2013 at 4:47 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I didn&#39;t realize I had postpartum depression until my baby was about one year old. I started coming out of that strange, horrible fog and started to realize &#8220;oh&#8230; that wasn&#39;t normal.&#8221; I&#39;m glad you&#39;re getting help sooner. I used to feel so confused because it was supposed to be natural, right? Like our bodies are biologically designed to conceive, labor, birth, feed, etc. but sometimes (most times?) it feel so incredibly unnatural. and hard. anyway, I wish you the best! My baby is now almost five, and it&#39;s incredible to me how much my heart just grows and grows everyday.</p>
<p>June is so sweet! So, so darling.</p>
    </div>

