  <li id="comment-39472" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39472"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-09T17:43:51-05:00">Wednesday, January 9, 2013 at 5:43 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;ve been reading you for years, your writing really resonates with me. This time, too: overwhelmed says it all. A long time has passed, my oldest son is now almost 14, but I vividly remember the despair of those first months. It helps when you finally surrender to the loss of control and the invasion of your thinking time. I believe it&#39;s a kind of mourning for the person you were. And while it&#39;s true that you will never be exactly the same, you will find yourself again, sooner than you might think. If I had to do it all over again, I&#39;d make sure I had more help, more sleep and more breaks from the baby. We expect too much, from ourselves and from others, and believe me, the details do not really matter much in the long run. You will all be fine, just different. And wiser.</p>
    </div>

