  <li id="comment-39480" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39480"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-09T20:31:22-05:00">Wednesday, January 9, 2013 at 8:31 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>You know, you are a brilliant and well rounded woman. I have watched your blog and book for quite awhile. I&#39;m sure your Dad is up there proud as he can be. Thank you for sharing.</p>
<p> The one thought I would like you and everyone to remember&#8230; hormones (all types) are some of the strongest and most mind altering substances in our bodies. If they can make us attempt to move a car off a person (cortisol), hide true amounts of bodily pain from our brains (oxytocin), and make men go into battle (testosterone), they can also cause mind altering amounts of painful feelings. Hence, it is perfectly understandable how they can disguise our true personalities while we are under their  spell.  We are immersed in hormone fog!!!<br />Just remember, the human spirit (brain off hormones) eventually comes out of any fog to a clearer day. :)) Big hug. </p>
    </div>

