  <li id="comment-39502" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/18034681635916434807" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Lucinda Richerson</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39502"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-11T16:48:07-05:00">Friday, January 11, 2013 at 4:48 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I remember feeling more completely overwhelmed than I have ever felt in my life, and being surprised by how dark some of my thoughts were (especially when I contrasted it with how happy I was supposed to be at this beautiful little baby that I oh so wanted) and how isolated I felt.  I suspect I had some form of postpartum depression, but did not get it diagnosed.  Certainly it is a time of soul-searching, transition, strong hormones, no sleep, worry, being needed 24/7 and a few other things I am forgetting &#8211; probably a hard combination to work though.  My daughter is almost 5 &#8211; we are still figuring things out (as it should  be), but that dark fog has lifted.  Wishing you the best, and thanks for your honest &#038; public sharing of thoughts / feelings.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
