  <li id="comment-39503" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">K</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39503"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-11T17:16:35-05:00">Friday, January 11, 2013 at 5:16 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have thought long and hard about writing this comment; so many others have written everything I have wanted to say and more, and have said it far better.<br />I too have been a long (long, long) time reader but have never commented. This entry touched so many nerves and raw feelings that it is hard to pinpoint exactly what I want to say. PPD runs rampant in my family; my grandmother spent the first few years of my mother&#39;s life in a mental institution. My own mother, while never diagnosed to my knowledge, was non-maternal at best. I fear these things to the ends of the earth, and am terrified to one day have children and experience them myself. It is a fear that wells deep down that I am afraid to name or speak aloud until read this entry. Thank you for giving voice to so many women&#39;s deep dark secrets, and for being okay with not being okay at this moment in time. <br />A great writer once wrote, &#8220;there is life after survival,&#8221; and I am relieved to see you learning just that, for both of our sake.</p>
<p>Thank you, Molly.</p>
    </div>

