  <li id="comment-39515" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39515"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-12T07:43:25-05:00">Saturday, January 12, 2013 at 7:43 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Just have to add to the roar: I was there too!  I didn&#39;t sleep for a week straight to the point where I was terrified to drive because I thought I would crash either from slowed reaction time or to make that crazy siren in my head keep from going off.  I&#39;d never had depression before and the whole thing really took me by surprise.  I was blissful being pregnant and so happy with my easy smiley wonderful little son.  But it hit me like a mac truck.  I went to a great psychiatrist after my sleepless week.  I took a very low dose of some drug that I forget the name of, and from that point on it all got steadily better.  You lose perspective completely in those first weeks and months, which you can know and do nothing about.  It&#39;s so frustrating.  You are brave to admit what you have been going through and I know it will be helpful to others.  I guess I was lead to believe it would all be some kind of blissful honeymoon full of adorable accessories and good smells.  NO no no no no. But it is real and beautiful in a fierce dark deep transformative way that I wouldn&#39;t trade.  My son&#39;s three now.  He&#39;s only gotten more smiley and phenomenal.  I wish you guys all the best.  Your daughter is absolutely gorgeous! </p>
    </div>

