  <li id="comment-39529" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/16345165456341197559" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Margo</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39529"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-14T15:44:00-05:00">Monday, January 14, 2013 at 3:44 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>dear Molly, I had postpartum depression after both my babies and both times it started as insomnia and progressed into severe anxiety which I did not understand was depression. The first time I thought my life was over, that I was going to be on drugs the rest of my life and unable to cope.  But both times, I was able to be on antidepressants for just 6 months, with self-care and talking to my family and best friend (never did find a therapist who was better than them!).</p>
<p>I vowed to tell my story to anybody who expressed the slightest interest OR slightest disparagement of mental illness.  I have done that.  Sometimes I even mention something when a pregnant friend wonders what being a new mom will be like &#8211; no one mentioned it to ME.  Naming things and being honest sets you free!</p>
<p>Thank you for telling your story.  I hope you come out of the fog soon and resume thinking there is hope and beauty in life.  Your little girl is so sweet.</p>
    </div>

