  <li id="comment-39547" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.ameliastudio.com" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">amy h</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39547"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-16T21:30:48-05:00">Wednesday, January 16, 2013 at 9:30 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I worried about the same thing when I was diagnosed with PPD after the birth of my middle child. I didn&#39;t want to be on antidepressants forever. I was on them for six months, then I gradually tapered off and didn&#39;t relapse. I will say that, for me, it always took about 1.5-2 years to feel totally myself after birth. This is mainly because I am an introverted creative person, and the littles don&#39;t allow much time for solitary creativity. It gets easier though. I&#39;m glad you recognized it and helped yourself!</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
