    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Greetings from Olympia! This was me with our first daughter. I knew something wasn&#39;t right when I found myself just wanting to give her to someone else to raise and go back to my &#8220;normal life.&#8221; I was so overwhelmed and nursing was hard and, you said it, I was full of crazy hormones. I was nervous it would happen again with our second daughter, but it didn&#39;t. I saw my daughter for a long time through the eyes of someone who connected her to that hard time, but now I see we &#8211; she &#8211; thrived in spite of the hardship. I feel like we triumphed in the face of a great storm together. We&#39;ve got your back, girl. And June is a stunner! Sending good thoughts northward to you. </p>
