      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39584"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-24T18:33:14-05:00">Thursday, January 24, 2013 at 6:33 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hi Molly &#8211;<br />I&#39;ve been reading your blog for a while and I love your writing.  You are an inspiration.  I had perfect baby boy 8 months ago and I felt <i>awful</i>.  There are so many &#8220;should&#8221; statements around childbirth and new motherhood, and for the first 4 months my experience was the opposite.  It&#39;s easy to tell ourselves that it&#39;s the hormones (and thank goodness that mecidine has come far enough that we know that!), but in the moment that&#39;s hardly a consolation.</p>
<p>Please know that you are SO strong to confront this and deal with it.  And that this shall pass and normalcy will return to your life.  Well&#8230;  At least a new kind of normalcy 🙂  But you <b>will</b> feel like <i>you</i> again.</p>
    </div>

