      <p>Pacific Northwest winters and a new babe&#8230;uugh, it almost seems unfair.  There should be bright pink flowers on all the trees and Disney bluebirds fluttering about. But no, just rain and darkness.  I went through the same thing with my second daughter and although I didn&#39;t read all 397 comments to make sure this advice hasn&#39;t already been given, I&#39;m going to run the risk of redundancy because it&#39;s so important:  DO NOT LISTEN TO COUNTRY MUSIC!  I&#39;m not even kidding.  In fact, I had to listen to only reggae for six months.  Seriously.<br />Also, juicing and listening to metaphysical podcasts.<br />It was ridiculous but also kind of sweet and gave me a little bit of mood busting light from within.<br />Thanks for being so honest.</p>
