  <li id="comment-39605" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Reade</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/ah-ha/#comment-39605"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-02-28T21:16:52-05:00">Thursday, February 28, 2013 at 9:16 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I see that you have already had such wonderful response, but i would like to share my experience as well.  I had (undiagnosed) post-partum with my first child, and I remember feeling so alone.  I don&#39;t need to explain the feeling to you, I know, but I do now share my experience with any expectant mother who I am close enough to share it with &#8211; not to scare them off, but to let them know that they are not alone, no matter how it may feel.<br />talking about it always helps.  I was so afraid of having postpartum the second time around that I nearly had anxiety attacks right after my son was born, until I realized that I had the tools to confront and handle it if it did happen&#8230;and then it dissipated.<br />thank you for your honest words, and your little June is so very dear!!</p>
    </div>

